---

# Answers (Optimized Solutions)
---

## Answer 1 — Previous Month Salary Change
SELECT emp_id,
       month,
       salary,
       LAG(salary) OVER(
           PARTITION BY emp_id
           ORDER BY month
       ) AS prev_salary,
       salary - LAG(salary) OVER(
           PARTITION BY emp_id
           ORDER BY month
       ) AS diff
FROM EmployeeSalary;
```
---

## Answer 2 — Next Login Date
SELECT user_id,
       login_date,
       LEAD(login_date) OVER(
           PARTITION BY user_id
           ORDER BY login_date
       ) AS next_login
FROM Logins;
```
---

## Answer 3 — Consecutive Login Gap
SELECT user_id,
       login_date,
       DATEDIFF(
         login_date,
         LAG(login_date) OVER(
             PARTITION BY user_id
             ORDER BY login_date
         )
       ) AS gap_days
FROM Logins;
```
---
## Answer 4 — First Order per Custome
WITH ranked AS (
SELECT *,
       ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
           PARTITION BY customer_id
           ORDER BY order_date
       ) rn
FROM Orders
)
SELECT order_id, customer_id, order_date
FROM ranked
WHERE rn = 1;
```---

## Answer 5 — Detect Salary Drop
WITH cte AS (
SELECT emp_id,
       month,
       salary,
       LAG(salary) OVER(
           PARTITION BY emp_id
           ORDER BY month
       ) AS prev_salary
FROM EmployeeSalary
)
SELECT *
FROM cte
WHERE salary < prev_salary;
```

